---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: "Apps"
description: "Bonfire is not a single app, but comes in many flavours..."
---

<div class="bg-base-300">
  <div class="max-w-screen-xl px-4 xl:px-0 flex flex-col mx-auto py-12">  
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold  ">Apps</h1>
    <h2 class="text-xl text-base-content mt-4 max-w-screen-sm">
Bonfire comes in diverse flavors, it's not a monolithic app. Tailor your experience by choosing the right one for your community, then enhance it further with extensions and themes for a perfect fit.</h2>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="max-w-screen-xl  px-4 xl:px-0  mx-auto my-12">
  <div class="grid xl:grid-cols-3 grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
   {% for item in apps %}
      <a href="/app/{{item.flavour}}">
      <div class="border border-base-content/30 rounded break-inside-avoid">
          <img src={{item.icon}} class="object-cover rounded-t mx-auto w-full h-80" />
          <div class="p-4">
            <h2 class="font-bold text-lg truncate word-break">{{item.name}}</h2>
            <p class="prose-sm mb-2">{{item.description}}</p>
          </div>
      </div>  
      </a>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>
</div>